1. Run zookeeper as normal go to:- kafka folder then run "bin/zookeeper-server-start.sh config/zookeeper.properties" 
2. To run zookeeper CLI run zookeeper and then in new terminal go to: kafka folder then run "bin/zookeeper-shell.sh localhost:2181"
3. To see all node run "ls /" in zookeeper CLI.
4. Other Commands as below
    .ls / to list the immediate children of the root znode.
    .ls /some_path to list the children of a specific znode.
    .get /some_znode to retrieve the data stored in a znode.
    .stat /some_znode to get the metadata (version, data length, etc.) of a znode.